Pre-requisites for OptiCrop: Smart Agricultural Production Optimization Engine (AI/ML)

Before developing the OptiCrop system, the following prerequisites are required:

1. Hardware Requirements
Computer/Laptop with at least Intel Core i5 or equivalent processor
Minimum 8 GB RAM (16 GB recommended)
20 GB free storage
Stable internet connection
Optional GPU (NVIDIA) for faster AI model training
2. Software Requirements
Operating System: Windows 10/11, Ubuntu, or macOS
Python 3.9 or above
Jupyter Notebook or Google Colab
Visual Studio Code or PyCharm
MySQL or PostgreSQL database
Git for version control
3. Programming Knowledge
Python programming
SQL and database management
HTML, CSS, JavaScript (for web interface)
Basic Flask or FastAPI framework
Machine Learning fundamentals
Deep Learning basics (CNN for disease detection)
4. AI/ML Libraries
NumPy
Pandas
Scikit-learn
TensorFlow/Keras
XGBoost
OpenCV
Matplotlib
Joblib
5. Datasets Required
Crop recommendation dataset
Soil nutrient dataset (N, P, K, pH)
Weather dataset (temperature, humidity, rainfall)
Crop yield dataset
Plant disease image dataset (e.g., PlantVillage)
Fertilizer recommendation dataset
6. Database Requirements
Farmer information
Farm and field details
Soil test records
Weather data
Crop information
Disease records
Recommendation history
7. APIs (Optional)
Weather API for real-time weather forecasts
Maps API for farm location visualization
SMS/Email API for sending farming alerts
8. Development Tools
GitHub for source code management
Postman for API testing
Docker (optional) for deployment
Streamlit or React (optional) for a user-friendly dashboard
9. Basic Domain Knowledge
Agriculture and crop cultivation
Soil science
Irrigation methods
Fertilizer management
Plant disease identification
Weather impacts on crop production
10. Expected Skills
Data preprocessing and cleaning
Feature engineering
Model training and evaluation
Database design
Web application development
Model deployment

These prerequisites provide the necessary foundation to successfully design, develop, train, and deploy the OptiCrop: Smart Agricultural Production Optimization Engine.
